<p>After graduating from Adana Tufanbeyli High School in 1985, he graduated from Marmara University's Department of International Relations in English in 1990. He started his business life in Transtren, which carried out international railway transportation activities in 1990-1991. In 1991-1992, he fulfilled his military obligation as a reserve officer in the Information Collection and Publishing Department of the Turkish Military Academy. He joined Arkas Holding in 1992 and worked in the maritime, highway, forwarding, logistics and railway departments, respectively. He undertook strategic tasks such as the establishment of the holding's railway network with railway terminals in different regions, the implementation of cabotage transports between Turkish ports by container ships, and the structuring of Arkas Logistics in the CIS countries. He has played a role in the development of special transportation equipment such as a generator trailer for hanging containers, reefer containers, transportation of bulk cargo with inner liner bag, flexitank and coiltainer. Since 2017, he has been serving as a member of the board of directors and general manager of STILL Arser, a partnership of the same holding with the German STILL GmbH, a material handling and warehouse equipment manufacturer.</p>
<p>In addition to being a board member of ISDER, the Association of Stacking Machinery Distributors and Manufacturers, he also teaches part-time Logistics in International Trade at the university.</p> 
